---
import ContentLayout from '@layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import Disclaimer from '@components/Disclaimer.astro';
import SafetyNote from '@components/SafetyNote.astro';
---
<ContentLayout title="About" eyebrow="Scope and purpose" description="What Hapkido Path is, who it is for, and how the content should be used." breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'About' }]}>
  <h2>What is this site?</h2>
  <p>This site is a structured Hapkido learning path and reference.</p>
  <p>It follows the names and progression used in my school where available, but it is not an official curriculum. Hapkido terminology, sequencing, and technique details vary across schools and federations.</p>

  <h2>Who is it for?</h2>
  <p>It is primarily built for my own study, but it is written in a way that can be shared with instructors or other students. It avoids private training journal content.</p>

  <h2>Is it official?</h2>
  <p>No. The technique names primarily follow the names used by my school. Where possible, I reserve space for references to Marc Tedeschi's Hapkido material or other sources, but I do not assume equivalence unless verified.</p>

  <h2>How should it be used?</h2>
  <p>The goal is to organize study notes, technique references, principles, and practice material in a clear way. Belt pages provide the path, lesson pages guide review, and technique pages hold the detailed mechanics.</p>

  <h2>What are the safety limitations?</h2>
  <p>The pages are detailed because they are intended to support self-study and review. They are not a substitute for qualified instruction, especially for joint locks, takedowns, pins, throws, or strikes.</p>
  <div class="grid grid-2"><Disclaimer /><SafetyNote /></div>
</ContentLayout>
